#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:5
msgid "Emscripten Compiler Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:7
msgid ""
"The following is a complete list of settings that can be passed to "
"emscripten via ``-s`` on the command line.  For example ``-sASSERTIONS`` or "
"``-sASSERTIONS=0``.  For more details see the :ref:`emcc <emcc-s-option-"
"value>` documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:12
msgid ""
"Unless otherwise noted these settings only apply when linking and have no "
"effect during compilation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:20
msgid "ASSERTIONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:22
msgid ""
"Whether we should add runtime assertions. This affects both JS and how "
"system libraries are built. ASSERTIONS == 2 gives even more runtime checks, "
"that may be very slow. That includes internal dlmalloc assertions, for "
"example. ASSERTIONS defaults to 0 in optimized builds (-O1 and above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:28
#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:369
#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:847
#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:863
