#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:1943
msgid "DYNAMIC_EXECUTION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:1945
msgid ""
"When set to 0, we do not emit eval() and new Function(), which disables some "
"functionality (causing runtime errors if attempted to be used), but allows "
"the emitted code to be acceptable in places that disallow dynamic code "
"execution (chrome packaged app, privileged firefox app, etc.). Pass this "
"flag when developing an Emscripten application that is targeting a "
"privileged or a certified execution environment, see Firefox Content "
"Security Policy (CSP) webpage for details: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-"
"US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy/script-src in particular "
"the 'unsafe-eval' and 'wasm-unsafe-eval' policies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:1955
msgid ""
"When this flag is set, the following features (linker flags) are unavailable:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:1957
