#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2531
msgid "PTHREAD_POOL_SIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2533
msgid ""
"In web browsers, Workers cannot be created while the main browser thread is "
"executing JS/Wasm code, but the main thread must regularly yield back to the "
"browser event loop for Worker initialization to occur. This means that "
"pthread_create() is essentially an asynchronous operation when called from "
"the main browser thread, and the main thread must repeatedly yield back to "
"the JS event loop in order for the thread to actually start. If your "
"application needs to be able to synchronously create new threads, you can "
"pre-create a pthread pool by specifying -sPTHREAD_POOL_SIZE=x, in which case "
"the specified number of Workers will be preloaded into a pool before the "
"application starts, and that many threads can then be available for "
"synchronous creation. Note that this setting is a string, and will be "
"emitted in the JS code (directly, with no extra quotes) so that if you set "
"it to '5' then 5 workers will be used in the pool, and so forth. The benefit "
"of this being a string is that you can set it to something like 'navigator."
"hardwareConcurrency' (which will use the number of cores the browser "
"reports, and is how you can get exactly enough workers for a threadpool "
"equal to the number of cores). [link] - affects generated JS runtime code at "
"link time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2559
msgid "PTHREAD_POOL_SIZE_STRICT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2561
msgid ""
"Normally, applications can create new threads even when the pool is empty. "
"When application breaks out to the JS event loop before trying to block on "
"the thread via ``pthread_join`` or any other blocking primitive, an extra "
"Worker will be created and the thread callback will be executed. However, "
"breaking out to the event loop requires custom modifications to the code to "
"adapt it to the Web, and not something that works for off-the-shelf apps. "
"Those apps without any modifications are most likely to deadlock. This "
"setting ensures that, instead of a risking a deadlock, they get a runtime "
"EAGAIN error instead that can at least be gracefully handled from the C / C+"
"+ side. Values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2573
msgid "``0`` - disable warnings on thread pool exhaustion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2574
msgid "``1`` - enable warnings on thread pool exhaustion (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2575
msgid "``2`` - make thread pool exhaustion a hard error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2582
msgid "PTHREAD_POOL_DELAY_LOAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2584
msgid ""
"If your application does not need the ability to synchronously create "
"threads, but it would still like to opportunistically speed up initial "
"thread startup time by prewarming a pool of Workers, you can specify the "
"size of the pool with -sPTHREAD_POOL_SIZE=x, but then also specify -"
"sPTHREAD_POOL_DELAY_LOAD, which will cause the runtime to not wait up at "
"startup for the Worker pool to finish loading. Instead, the runtime will "
"immediately start up and the Worker pool will asynchronously spin up in "
"parallel on the background. This can shorten the time that pthread_create() "
"calls take to actually start a thread, but without actually slowing down "
"main application startup speed. If PTHREAD_POOL_DELAY_LOAD=0 (default), then "
"the runtime will wait for the pool to start up before running main(). If you "
"do need to synchronously wait on the created threads (e.g. via "
"pthread_join), you must wait on the Module.pthreadPoolReady promise before "
"doing so or you're very likely to run into deadlocks. [link] - affects "
"generated JS runtime code at link time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2605
msgid "DEFAULT_PTHREAD_STACK_SIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2607
msgid ""
"Default stack size to use for newly created pthreads.  When not set, this "
"defaults to STACK_SIZE (which in turn defaults to 64k).  Can also be set at "
"runtime using pthread_attr_setstacksize().  Note that the wasm control flow "
"stack is separate from this stack.  This stack only contains certain "
"function local variables, such as those that have their addresses taken, or "
"ones that are too large to fit as local vars in wasm code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2619
msgid "PTHREADS_PROFILING"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2621
msgid "True when building with --threadprofiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2628
msgid "ALLOW_BLOCKING_ON_MAIN_THREAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2630
msgid ""
"It is dangerous to call pthread_join or pthread_cond_wait on the main "
"thread, as doing so can cause deadlocks on the Web (and also it works using "
"a busy-wait which is expensive). See https://emscripten.org/docs/porting/"
"pthreads.html#blocking-on-the-main-browser-thread This may become set to 0 "
"by default in the future; for now, this just warns in the console."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2642
#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3311
msgid "PTHREADS_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2644
msgid "If true, add in debug traces for diagnosing pthreads related issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2651
msgid "EVAL_CTORS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2653
msgid ""
"This tries to evaluate code at compile time. The main use case is to eval "
"global ctor functions, which are those that run before main(), but main() "
"itself or parts of it can also be evalled. Evaluating code this way can "
"avoid work at runtime, as it applies the results of the execution to memory "
"and globals and so forth, \"snapshotting\" the wasm and then just running it "
"from there when it is loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2660
msgid ""
"This will stop when it sees something it cannot eval at compile time, like a "
"call to an import. When running with this option you will see logging that "
"indicates what is evalled and where it stops."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2664
msgid ""
"This optimization can either reduce or increase code size. If a small amount "
"of code generates many changes in memory, for example, then overall size may "
"increase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2668
msgid ""
"LLVM's GlobalOpt *almost* does this operation. It does in simple cases, "
"where LLVM IR is not too complex for its logic to evaluate, but it isn't "
"powerful enough for e.g. libc++ iostream ctors. It is just hard to do at the "
"LLVM IR level - LLVM IR is complex and getting more complex, so this would "
"require GlobalOpt to have a full interpreter, plus a way to write back into "
"LLVM IR global objects.  At the wasm level, however, everything has been "
"lowered into a simple low level, and we also just need to write bytes into "
"an array, so this is easy for us to do. A further issue for LLVM is that it "
"doesn't know that we will not link in further code, so it only tries to "
"optimize ctors with lowest priority (while we do know explicitly if dynamic "
"linking is enabled or not)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2680
msgid ""
"If set to a value of 2, this also makes some \"unsafe\" assumptions, "
"specifically that there is no input received while evalling ctors. That "
"means we ignore args to main() as well as assume no environment vars are "
"readable. This allows more programs to be optimized, but you need to make "
"sure your program does not depend on those features - even just checking the "
"value of argc can lead to problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2692
msgid "TEXTDECODER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2694
msgid ""
"The default value or 1 means the generated code will use TextDecoder if "
"available and fall back to custom decoder code when not available. If set to "
"2, we assume TextDecoder is present and usable, and do not emit any JS code "
"to fall back if it is missing. Setting this zero to avoid even conditional "
"usage of TextDecoder is no longer supported. Note: In -Oz builds, the "
"default value of TEXTDECODER is set to 2, to save on code size (except when "
"AUDIO_WORKLET is specified, or when `shell` is part of ENVIRONMENT since "
"TextDecoder is not available in those environments)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2708
msgid "EMBIND_STD_STRING_IS_UTF8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2710
msgid ""
"Embind specific: If enabled, assume UTF-8 encoded data in std::string "
"binding. Disable this to support binary data transfer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2718
msgid "EMBIND_AOT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2720
msgid ""
"Embind specific: If enabled, generate Embind's JavaScript invoker functions "
"at compile time and include them in the JS output file. When used with "
"DYNAMIC_EXECUTION=0 this allows exported bindings to be just as fast as "
"DYNAMIC_EXECUTION=1 mode, but without the need for eval(). If there are many "
"bindings the JS output size may be larger though."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2731
msgid "OFFSCREENCANVAS_SUPPORT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2733
msgid ""
"If set to 1, enables support for transferring canvases to pthreads and "
"creating WebGL contexts in them, as well as explicit swap control for GL "
"contexts. This needs browser support for the OffscreenCanvas specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2742
msgid "OFFSCREENCANVASES_TO_PTHREAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2744
msgid ""
"If you are using PROXY_TO_PTHREAD with OFFSCREENCANVAS_SUPPORT, then specify "
"here a comma separated list of CSS ID selectors to canvases to proxy over to "
"the pthread at program startup, e.g. '#canvas1, #canvas2'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2748
msgid "Default value: \"#canvas\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2753
msgid "OFFSCREEN_FRAMEBUFFER"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2755
msgid ""
"If set to 1, enables support for WebGL contexts to render to an offscreen "
"render target, to avoid the implicit swap behavior of WebGL where exiting "
"any event callback would automatically perform a \"flip\" to present "
"rendered content on screen. When an Emscripten GL context has Offscreen "
"Framebuffer enabled, a single frame can be composited from multiple event "
"callbacks, and the swap function emscripten_webgl_commit_frame() is then "
"explicitly called to present the rendered content on screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2763
msgid ""
"The OffscreenCanvas feature also enables explicit GL frame swapping support, "
"and also, -sOFFSCREEN_FRAMEBUFFER feature can be used to polyfill support "
"for accessing WebGL in multiple threads in the absence of OffscreenCanvas "
"support in browser, at the cost of some performance and latency. "
"OffscreenCanvas and Offscreen Framebuffer support can be enabled at the same "
"time, and allows one to utilize OffscreenCanvas where available, and to fall "
"back to Offscreen Framebuffer otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2776
msgid "FETCH_SUPPORT_INDEXEDDB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2778
msgid ""
"If nonzero, Fetch API supports backing to IndexedDB. If 0, IndexedDB is not "
"utilized. Set to 0 if IndexedDB support is not interesting for target "
"application, to save a few kBytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2787
#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3320
msgid "FETCH_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2789
msgid "If nonzero, prints out debugging information in library_fetch.js"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2796
msgid "FETCH"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2798
msgid "If nonzero, enables emscripten_fetch API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2805
msgid "FETCH_STREAMING"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2807
msgid ""
"Enables streaming fetched data when the fetch attribute "
"EMSCRIPTEN_FETCH_STREAM_DATA is used. For streaming requests, the DOM Fetch "
"API is used otherwise XMLHttpRequest is used. Both modes generally support "
"the same API, but there are some key differences:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2813
msgid "XHR supports synchronous requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2814
msgid "XHR supports overriding mime types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2815
msgid "Fetch supports streaming data using the 'onprogress' callback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2817
msgid ""
"If set to a value of 2, only the DOM Fetch backend will be used. This should "
"only be used in testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2825
msgid "WASMFS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2827
msgid ""
"ATTENTION [WIP]: Experimental feature. Please use at your own risk. This "
"will eventually replace the current JS file system implementation. If set to "
"1, uses new filesystem implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2838
msgid "SINGLE_FILE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2840
msgid ""
"If set to 1, embeds all subresources in the emitted file as base64 string "
"literals. Embedded subresources may include (but aren't limited to) wasm, "
"asm.js, and static memory initialization code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2844
msgid ""
"When using code that depends on this option, your Content Security Policy "
"may need to be updated. Specifically, embedding asm.js requires the script-"
"src directive to allow 'unsafe-inline', and using a Worker requires the "
"child-src directive to allow blob:. If you aren't using Content Security "
"Policy, or your CSP header doesn't include either script-src or child-src, "
"then you can safely ignore this warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2851
msgid ""
"Note that SINGLE_FILE with binary encoding requires the HTML/JS files to be "
"served with UTF-8 encoding. See the details on SINGLE_FILE_BINARY_ENCODE."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2859
msgid "SINGLE_FILE_BINARY_ENCODE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2861
msgid ""
"If true, binary Wasm content is encoded using a custom UTF-8 embedding "
"instead of base64. This generates a smaller binary that compresses well. Set "
"this to false to revert back to earlier base64 encoding if you run into "
"issues with the binary encoding. (and please let us know of any such issues) "
"If no issues arise, this option will permanently become the default in the "
"future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2868
msgid ""
"NOTE: Binary encoding requires that the HTML/JS files are served with UTF-8 "
"encoding, and will not work with the default legacy Windows-1252 encoding "
"that browsers might use on Windows. To enable UTF-8 encoding in a hand-"
"crafted index.html file, apply any of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2873
msgid "Add `<meta charset=\"utf-8\">` inside the <head> section of HTML, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2874
msgid ""
"Add `<meta http-equiv=\"content-type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" /"
">`` inside <head>, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2875
msgid ""
"Add `<meta http-equiv=\"content-type\" content=\"application/json; "
"charset=utf-8\" />` inside <head> (if using -o foo.js with SINGLE_FILE mode "
"to build HTML+JS), or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2877
msgid ""
"pass the header `Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8` and/or header "
"`Content-Type: application/javascript; charset=utf-8` when serving the "
"relevant files that contain binary encoded content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2881
msgid ""
"If none of these are possible, disable binary encoding with -"
"sSINGLE_FILE_BINARY_ENCODE=0 to fall back to base64 encoding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2889
msgid "AUTO_JS_LIBRARIES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2891
msgid ""
"If set to 1, all JS libraries will be automatically available at link time. "
"This gets set to 0 in STRICT mode (or with MINIMAL_RUNTIME) which mean you "
"need to explicitly specify -lfoo.js in at link time in order to access "
"library function in library_foo.js."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2901
msgid "AUTO_NATIVE_LIBRARIES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2903
msgid ""
"Like AUTO_JS_LIBRARIES but for the native libraries such as libgl, libal and "
"libhtml5.   If this is disabled it is necessary to explicitly add e.g. -"
"lhtml5 and also to first build the library using ``embuilder``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2912
msgid "MIN_FIREFOX_VERSION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2914
msgid ""
"Specifies the oldest major version of Firefox to target. I.e. all Firefox "
"versions >= MIN_FIREFOX_VERSION are desired to work. Pass -"
"sMIN_FIREFOX_VERSION=majorVersion to drop support for Firefox versions older "
"than majorVersion. Firefox 79 was released on 2020-07-28. MAX_INT "
"(0x7FFFFFFF, or -1) specifies that target is not supported. Minimum "
"supported value is 68 which was released on 2019-07-09 (see feature_matrix."
"py)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2923
msgid "Default value: 79"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2928
msgid "MIN_SAFARI_VERSION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2930
msgid ""
"Specifies the oldest version of desktop Safari to target. Version is encoded "
"in MMmmVV, e.g. 160101 denotes Safari 16.1.1. Safari 15 was released on "
"September 20, 2021, bundled with macOS 12.0 Monterey and iOS 15. NOTE: "
"Emscripten is unable to produce code that would work in iOS 9.3.5 and older, "
"i.e. iPhone 4s, iPad 2, iPad 3, iPad Mini 1, Pod Touch 5 and older, see "
"https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/pull/7191. MAX_INT "
"(0x7FFFFFFF, or -1) specifies that target is not supported. Minimum "
"supported value is 140100 which was released on 2021-04-26 (see "
"feature_matrix.py)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2941
msgid "Default value: 150000"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2946
msgid "MIN_CHROME_VERSION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2948
msgid ""
"Specifies the oldest version of Chrome. E.g. pass -sMIN_CHROME_VERSION=100 "
"to drop support for Chrome 99 and older. This setting also applies to modern "
"Chromium-based Edge, which shares version numbers with Chrome. Chrome 85 was "
"released on 2020-08-25. MAX_INT (0x7FFFFFFF, or -1) specifies that target is "
"not supported. Minimum supported value is 85, which was released on "
"2020-08-25 (see feature_matrix.py)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2957
msgid "Default value: 85"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2962
msgid "MIN_NODE_VERSION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2964
msgid ""
"Specifies minimum node version to target for the generated code.  This is "
"distinct from the minimum version required to run the emscripten compiler. "
"Version is encoded in MMmmVV, e.g. 181401 denotes Node 18.14.01. Minimum "
"supported value is 180300, which was released 2022-05-18 (see feature_matrix."
"py). This version aligns with the version available in debian/stable "
"(bookworm)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2971
msgid "Default value: 180300"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2976
msgid "MINIMAL_RUNTIME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2978
msgid ""
"If true, uses minimal sized runtime without POSIX features, Module, preRun/"
"preInit/etc., Emscripten built-in XHR loading or library_browser.js. Enable "
"this setting to target the smallest code size possible.  Set "
"MINIMAL_RUNTIME=2 to further enable even more code size optimizations. These "
"opts are quite hacky, and work around limitations in Closure and other parts "
"of the build system, so they may not work in all generated programs (But can "
"be useful for really small programs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2986
msgid ""
"By default, no symbols will be exported on the ``Module`` object. In order "
"to export kept alive symbols, please use ``-sEXPORT_KEEPALIVE=1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2994
msgid "MINIMAL_RUNTIME_STREAMING_WASM_COMPILATION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:2996
msgid ""
"If set to 1, MINIMAL_RUNTIME will utilize streaming WebAssembly compilation, "
"where WebAssembly module is compiled already while it is being downloaded. "
"In order for this to work, the web server MUST properly serve the .wasm file "
"with a HTTP response header \"Content-Type: application/wasm\". If this HTTP "
"header is not present, e.g. Firefox 73 will fail with an error message "
"``TypeError: Response has unsupported MIME type`` and Chrome 78 will fail "
"with an error message `Uncaught (in promise) TypeError: Failed to execute "
"'compile' on 'WebAssembly': Incorrect response MIME type. Expected "
"'application/wasm'`. If set to 0 (default), streaming WebAssembly "
"compilation is disabled, which means that the WebAssembly Module will first "
"be downloaded fully, and only then compilation starts. For large .wasm "
"modules and production environments, this should be set to 1 for faster "
"startup speeds. However this setting is disabled by default since it "
"requires server side configuration and for really small pages there is no "
"observable difference (also has a ~100 byte impact to code size) This "
"setting is only compatible with html output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3019
msgid "MINIMAL_RUNTIME_STREAMING_WASM_INSTANTIATION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3021
msgid ""
"If set to 1, MINIMAL_RUNTIME will utilize streaming WebAssembly "
"instantiation, where WebAssembly module is compiled+instantiated already "
"while it is being downloaded. Same restrictions/requirements apply as with "
"MINIMAL_RUNTIME_STREAMING_WASM_COMPILATION. "
"MINIMAL_RUNTIME_STREAMING_WASM_COMPILATION and "
"MINIMAL_RUNTIME_STREAMING_WASM_INSTANTIATION cannot be simultaneously "
"active. Which one of these two is faster depends on the size of the wasm "
"module, the size of the JS runtime file, and the size of the preloaded data "
"file to download, and the browser in question."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3036
msgid "SUPPORT_LONGJMP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3038
msgid ""
"If set to 'emscripten' or 'wasm', compiler supports setjmp() and longjmp(). "
"If set to 0, these APIs are not available.  If you are using C++ exceptions, "
"but do not need setjmp()+longjmp() API, then you can set this to 0 to save a "
"little bit of code size and performance when catching exceptions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3043
msgid ""
"'emscripten': (default) Emscripten setjmp/longjmp handling using JavaScript "
"'wasm': setjmp/longjmp handling using Wasm EH instructions (experimental)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3046
msgid "0: No setjmp/longjmp handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3047
msgid ""
"1: Default setjmp/longjmp/handling, depending on the mode of exceptions. "
"'wasm' if '-fwasm-exceptions' is used, 'emscripten' otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3050
msgid ""
"At compile time this enables the transformations needed for longjmp support "
"at codegen time, while at link it allows linking in the library support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3060
msgid "DISABLE_DEPRECATED_FIND_EVENT_TARGET_BEHAVIOR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3062
msgid ""
"If set to 1, disables old deprecated HTML5 API event target lookup behavior. "
"When enabled, there is no \"Module.canvas\" object, no magic \"null\" "
"default handling, and DOM element 'target' parameters are taken to refer to "
"CSS selectors, instead of referring to DOM IDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3072
msgid "HTML5_SUPPORT_DEFERRING_USER_SENSITIVE_REQUESTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3074
msgid ""
"Certain browser DOM API operations, such as requesting fullscreen mode "
"transition or pointer lock require that the request originates from within a "
"user initiated event, such as mouse click or keyboard press. Refactoring an "
"application to follow this kind of program structure can be difficult, so "
"HTML5_SUPPORT_DEFERRING_USER_SENSITIVE_REQUESTS allows transparent emulation "
"of this by deferring such requests until a suitable event callback is "
"generated. Set this to 0 to disable support for deferring to save code size "
"if your application does not need support for deferred calls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3088
msgid "MINIFY_HTML"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3090
msgid ""
"Specifies whether the generated .html file is run through html-minifier. The "
"set of optimization passes run by html-minifier depends on debug and "
"optimization levels. In -g2 and higher, no minification is performed. In -"
"g1, minification is done, but whitespace is retained. Minification requires "
"at least -O1 or -Os to be used. Pass -sMINIFY_HTML=0 to explicitly choose to "
"disable HTML minification altogether."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3102
msgid "ASAN_SHADOW_SIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3104
msgid ""
"This option is no longer used. The appropriate shadow memory size is now "
"calculated from INITIAL_MEMORY and MAXIMUM_MEMORY. Will be removed in a "
"future release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3113
msgid "SOURCE_MAP_PREFIXES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3115
msgid ""
"List of path substitutions to apply in the \"sources\" field of the source "
"map. Corresponds to the ``--prefix`` option used in ``tools/wasm-sourcemap."
"py``. Must be used with ``-gsource-map``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3119
msgid ""
"This setting allows to map path prefixes to the proper ones so that the "
"final (possibly relative) URLs point to the correct locations : ``-"
"sSOURCE_MAP_PREFIXES=/old/path=/new/path``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3128
msgid "DEFAULT_TO_CXX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3130
msgid ""
"Default to c++ mode even when run as ``emcc`` rather than ``emc++``. When "
"this is disabled ``em++`` is required when linking C++ programs. Disabling "
"this will match the behaviour of gcc/g++ and clang/clang++."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3139
msgid "PRINTF_LONG_DOUBLE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3141
msgid ""
"While LLVM's wasm32 has long double = float128, we don't support printing "
"that at full precision by default. Instead we print as 64-bit doubles, which "
"saves libc code size. You can flip this option on to get a libc with full "
"long double printing precision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3151
msgid "SEPARATE_DWARF_URL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3153
msgid ""
"Setting this affects the path emitted in the wasm that refers to the DWARF "
"file, in -gseparate-dwarf mode. This allows the debugging file to be hosted "
"in a custom location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3157
msgid "Default value: ''"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3162
msgid "ERROR_ON_WASM_CHANGES_AFTER_LINK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3164
msgid ""
"Emscripten runs wasm-ld to link, and in some cases will do further changes "
"to the wasm afterwards, like running wasm-opt to optimize the binary in "
"optimized builds. However, in some builds no wasm changes are necessary "
"after link. This can make the entire link step faster, and can also be "
"important for other reasons, like in debugging if the wasm is not modified "
"then the DWARF info from LLVM is preserved (wasm-opt can rewrite it in some "
"cases, but not in others like split-dwarf). When this flag is turned on, we "
"error at link time if the build requires any changes to the wasm after link. "
"This can be useful in testing, for example. Some example of features that "
"require post-link wasm changes are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3175
msgid "Lowering i64 to i32 pairs at the JS boundary (See WASM_BIGINT)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3176
msgid ""
"Lowering nontrapping-float-to-int operations when targeting older browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3183
msgid "ABORT_ON_WASM_EXCEPTIONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3185
msgid ""
"Abort on unhandled exceptions that occur when calling exported WebAssembly "
"functions. This makes the program behave more like a native program where "
"the OS would terminate the process and no further code can be executed when "
"an unhandled exception (e.g. out-of-bounds memory access) happens. This will "
"instrument all exported functions to catch thrown exceptions and call "
"abort() when they happen. Once the program aborts any exported function "
"calls will fail with a \"program has already aborted\" exception to prevent "
"calls into code with a potentially corrupted program state. This adds a "
"small fixed amount to code size in optimized builds and a slight overhead "
"for the extra instrumented function indirection.  Enable this if you want "
"Emscripten to handle unhandled exceptions nicely at the cost of a few bytes "
"extra. Exceptions that occur within the ``main`` function are already "
"handled via an alternative mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3205
msgid "PURE_WASI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3207
msgid ""
"Build binaries that use as many WASI APIs as possible, and include "
"additional JS support libraries for those APIs.  This allows emscripten to "
"produce binaries that are more WASI compliant and also allows it to process "
"and execute WASI binaries built with other SDKs (e.g.  wasi-sdk). This "
"setting is experimental and subject to change or removal. Implies :ref:"
"`STANDALONE_WASM`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3221
msgid "IMPORTED_MEMORY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3223
msgid ""
"Set to 1 to define the WebAssembly.Memory object outside of the wasm "
"module.  By default the wasm module defines the memory and exports it to "
"JavaScript. Use of the following settings will enable this settings since "
"they depend on being able to define the memory in JavaScript:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3229
msgid "-pthread"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3230
msgid "RELOCATABLE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3231
msgid "ASYNCIFY_LAZY_LOAD_CODE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3232
msgid "WASM2JS (WASM=0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3239
msgid "SPLIT_MODULE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3241
msgid ""
"Generate code to load split wasm modules. This option will automatically "
"generate two wasm files as output, one with the ``.orig`` suffix and one "
"without.  The default file (without the suffix) when run will generate "
"instrumentation data that can later be fed into wasm-split (the binaryen "
"tool). As well as this the generated JS code will contain helper functions "
"to load split modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3256
msgid "AUTOLOAD_DYLIBS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3258
msgid ""
"For MAIN_MODULE builds, automatically load any dynamic library dependencies "
"on startup, before loading the main module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3266
msgid "ALLOW_UNIMPLEMENTED_SYSCALLS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3268
msgid ""
"Link against stub implementations of unsupported/unimplemented syscalls. "
"This allows programs that depend on these syscalls to be compiled, even "
"though these functions will fail (or do nothing) at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3277
msgid "TRUSTED_TYPES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3279
msgid ""
"Allow calls to Worker(...) and importScripts(...) to be Trusted Types "
"compatible. Trusted Types is a Web Platform feature designed to mitigate DOM "
"XSS by restricting the usage of DOM sink APIs. See https://w3c.github.io/"
"webappsec-trusted-types/."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3289
msgid "POLYFILL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3291
msgid ""
"When targeting older browsers emscripten will sometimes require that "
"polyfills be included in the output.  If you would prefer to take care of "
"polyfilling yourself via some other mechanism you can prevent emscripten "
"from generating these by passing ``-sNO_POLYFILL`` or ``-sPOLYFILL=0`` With "
"default browser targets emscripten does not need any polyfills so this "
"settings is *only* needed when also explicitly targeting older browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3303
msgid "RUNTIME_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3305
msgid ""
"If non-zero, add tracing to core runtime functions.  Can be set to 2 for "
"extra tracing (for example, tracing that occurs on each turn of the event "
"loop or each user callback, which can flood the console). This setting is "
"enabled by default if any of the following debugging settings are enabled:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3327
msgid "LEGACY_RUNTIME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3329
msgid ""
"Include JS library symbols that were previously part of the default runtime. "
"Without this, such symbols can be made available by adding them to :ref:"
"`DEFAULT_LIBRARY_FUNCS_TO_INCLUDE`, or via the dependencies of another JS "
"library symbol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3339
msgid "SIGNATURE_CONVERSIONS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3341
msgid ""
"User-defined functions to wrap with signature conversion, which take or "
"return pointer arguments. Only affects ``MEMORY64=1`` builds, see "
"``create_pointer_conversion_wrappers`` in ``emscripten.py`` for details. Use "
"``_`` for non-pointer arguments, ``p`` for pointer/i53 arguments, and ``P`` "
"for optional pointer/i53 values. Example use ``-"
"sSIGNATURE_CONVERSIONS=someFunction:_p,anotherFunction:p``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3353
msgid "WASM_BINDGEN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3355
msgid ""
"Run wasm-bindgen and integrate the rust-exported symbols into the rest of "
"Emscripten's JS output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3362
msgid "SOURCE_PHASE_IMPORTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3364
msgid ""
"Experimental support for wasm source phase imports. This is only currently "
"implemented in the pre-release/nightly version of node, and not yet "
"supported by browsers. Requires EXPORT_ES6"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3376
msgid "WASM_ESM_INTEGRATION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3378
msgid ""
"Experimental support for wasm ESM integration. Requires :ref:`EXPORT_ES6` "
"and ``MODULARIZE=instance``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3388
msgid "JS_BASE64_API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3390
msgid ""
"Enable use of the JS arraybuffer-base64 API: https://github.com/tc39/"
"proposal-arraybuffer-base64 To run the resulting code currently requires "
"passing `--js_base_64` to node or chrome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3402
msgid "GROWABLE_ARRAYBUFFERS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3404
msgid ""
"Enable support for growable views of Wasm memory. This is a recent Web "
"platform feature that can make growing the Wasm memory more efficient, "
"especially in multi-threaded builds. Setting this to 1 will auto-detect the "
"presence of this API and use it when available. Setting this to 2 will "
"unconditionally require it. This is the only way to completely remove the "
"overhead of growable memory + pthreads. This settings does nothing unless "
"ALLOW_MEMORY_GROWTH is set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3418
msgid "CROSS_ORIGIN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3420
msgid ""
"If the emscripten-generated program is hosted on separate origin then "
"starting new pthread worker can violate CSP rules.  Enabling CROSS_ORIGIN "
"uses an inline worker to instead load the worker script indirectly using "
"`importScripts`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3430
msgid "CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3432
msgid ""
"Enables Cross-Origin Storage (COS) API support for Wasm loading on the Web "
"target. At link time Emscripten computes the SHA-256 hash of the final ``."
"wasm`` binary and embeds it in the generated JS. At runtime the COS API is "
"used as a progressive enhancement: the binary is fetched from the shared "
"cross-origin cache on a hit, or stored there after a network fetch on a "
"miss; when the API is absent or errors the runtime falls through to the "
"standard fetch path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3440
msgid ""
"Requires the Web environment; using it without ``-sENVIRONMENT=web`` is a "
"hard link-time error. Incompatible with SINGLE_FILE and "
"WASM_ASYNC_COMPILATION=0 (both produce hard link-time errors)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3444
msgid "See :ref:`CrossOriginStorage` for the full guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3453
msgid "CROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE_ORIGINS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3455
msgid ""
"Controls which origins may read the Wasm binary from the COS cache. Only "
"meaningful when ``-sCROSS_ORIGIN_STORAGE`` is set. Applied only during the "
"write (cache-miss) path, not the read (cache-hit) path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3459
msgid ""
"``['*']`` (default) — any origin can retrieve the file. Explicit HTTPS "
"origin list — restricted to those origins only::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3464
msgid "``[]`` — same-site only (omits the ``origins`` field entirely)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3466
msgid "Mixing ``'*'`` with explicit origins is a link-time error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3468
msgid "Default value: ['*']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3473
msgid "FAKE_DYLIBS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3475
msgid ""
"This setting changes the behaviour of the ``-shared`` flag.  When set to "
"true you get the old emscripten behaviour where the ``-shared`` flag "
"actually produces a normal object file (i.e. ``ld -r``).  When set to true "
"(the default) the ``-shared`` flag is equivelent to :ref:`SIDE_MODULE` and "
"will produce a Wasn dynamic library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3486
msgid "EXECUTABLE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3488
msgid ""
"Add a #! line to generated JS file and make it executable.  This is useful "
"for building command line tools that run under node. This setting can also "
"be set to a string value, in which case that string will be used as the #! "
"command to embed in the generated file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3499
msgid "Deprecated Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3501
msgid ""
"The following settings have been proposed for removal from emscripten.  "
"These settings still function but may be removed in a future version.  If "
"your project is using one of these settings please open a bug (or reply to "
"one of the existing bugs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3505
msgid ""
"``RUNTIME_LINKED_LIBS``: you can simply list the libraries directly on the "
"commandline now"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3506
msgid "``CLOSURE_WARNINGS``: use -Wclosure/-Wno-closure instead"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3507
msgid ""
"``LEGALIZE_JS_FFI``: to disable JS type legalization use `-sWASM_BIGINT` or "
"`-sSTANDALONE_WASM`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3508
msgid "``ASYNCIFY_EXPORTS``: please use JSPI_EXPORTS instead"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3509
msgid ""
"``LINKABLE``: under consideration for removal (https://github.com/emscripten-"
"core/emscripten/issues/25262)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3510
msgid ""
"``EXPORT_EXCEPTION_HANDLING_HELPERS``: getExceptionMessage is exported "
"anyway when ASSERTIONS or EXCEPTION_STACK_TRACES is set, which are set by "
"default at -O0. At -O1 or above, you can export it separately by -"
"sEXPORTED_RUNTIME_METHODS=getExceptionMessage,decrementExceptionRefcount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3511
msgid ""
"``DETERMINISTIC``: under consideration for removal (https://github.com/"
"emscripten-core/emscripten/issues/26647)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3512
msgid "``USE_PTHREADS``: prefer the standard -pthread flag"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3513
msgid "``MEMORY64``: prefer the standard -m64 or --target=wasm64 flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3519
msgid "Legacy Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3521
msgid ""
"The following settings no longer have any effect but are still accepted by "
"emscripten for backwards compatibility with older versions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3524
msgid "``BINARYEN``: Valid values: WASM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3525
msgid "``TOTAL_STACK``: Valid values: STACK_SIZE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3526
msgid "``BINARYEN_ASYNC_COMPILATION``: Valid values: WASM_ASYNC_COMPILATION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3527
msgid ""
"``UNALIGNED_MEMORY``: forced unaligned memory not supported in fastcomp "
"(Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3528
msgid ""
"``FORCE_ALIGNED_MEMORY``: forced aligned memory is not supported in fastcomp "
"(Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3529
msgid "``PGO``: pgo no longer supported (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3530
msgid ""
"``QUANTUM_SIZE``: altering the QUANTUM_SIZE is not supported (Valid values: "
"[4])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3531
msgid ""
"``FUNCTION_POINTER_ALIGNMENT``: Starting from Emscripten 1.37.29, no longer "
"available (https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/pull/6091) (Valid "
"values: [2])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3532
msgid "``RESERVED_FUNCTION_POINTERS``: Valid values: ALLOW_TABLE_GROWTH"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3533
msgid ""
"``BUILD_AS_SHARED_LIB``: Starting from Emscripten 1.38.16, no longer "
"available (https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/pull/7433) (Valid "
"values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3534
msgid ""
"``SAFE_SPLIT_MEMORY``: Starting from Emscripten 1.38.19, SAFE_SPLIT_MEMORY "
"codegen is no longer available (https://github.com/emscripten-core/"
"emscripten/pull/7465) (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3535
msgid ""
"``SPLIT_MEMORY``: Starting from Emscripten 1.38.19, SPLIT_MEMORY codegen is "
"no longer available (https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/"
"pull/7465) (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3536
msgid ""
"``BINARYEN_METHOD``: Starting from Emscripten 1.38.23, Emscripten now always "
"builds either to Wasm (-sWASM - default), or to JavaScript (-sWASM=0), other "
"methods are not supported (https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/"
"pull/7836) (Valid values: ['native-wasm'])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3537
msgid ""
"``BINARYEN_TRAP_MODE``: The wasm backend does not support a trap mode (it "
"always clamps, in effect) (Valid values: [-1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3538
msgid ""
"``PRECISE_I64_MATH``: Starting from Emscripten 1.38.26, PRECISE_I64_MATH is "
"always enabled (https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/pull/7935) "
"(Valid values: [1, 2])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3539
msgid ""
"``MEMFS_APPEND_TO_TYPED_ARRAYS``: Starting from Emscripten 1.38.26, "
"MEMFS_APPEND_TO_TYPED_ARRAYS=0 is no longer supported. MEMFS no longer "
"supports using JS arrays for file data (https://github.com/emscripten-core/"
"emscripten/pull/7918) (Valid values: [1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3540
msgid ""
"``ERROR_ON_MISSING_LIBRARIES``: missing libraries are always an error now "
"(Valid values: [1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3541
msgid ""
"``EMITTING_JS``: The new STANDALONE_WASM flag replaces this (replace "
"EMITTING_JS=0 with STANDALONE_WASM=1) (Valid values: [1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3542
msgid ""
"``SKIP_STACK_IN_SMALL``: SKIP_STACK_IN_SMALL is no longer needed as the "
"backend can optimize it directly (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3543
msgid ""
"``SAFE_STACK``: Replace SAFE_STACK=1 with STACK_OVERFLOW_CHECK=2 (Valid "
"values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3544
msgid "``MEMORY_GROWTH_STEP``: Valid values: MEMORY_GROWTH_LINEAR_STEP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3545
msgid ""
"``ELIMINATE_DUPLICATE_FUNCTIONS``: Duplicate function elimination for wasm "
"is handled automatically by binaryen (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3546
msgid ""
"``ELIMINATE_DUPLICATE_FUNCTIONS_DUMP_EQUIVALENT_FUNCTIONS``: Duplicate "
"function elimination for wasm is handled automatically by binaryen (Valid "
"values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3547
msgid ""
"``ELIMINATE_DUPLICATE_FUNCTIONS_PASSES``: Duplicate function elimination for "
"wasm is handled automatically by binaryen (Valid values: [5])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3548
msgid ""
"``WASM_OBJECT_FILES``: For LTO, use -flto or -fto=thin instead. Otherwise, "
"Wasm object files are the default (Valid values: [1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3549
msgid "``TOTAL_MEMORY``: Valid values: INITIAL_MEMORY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3550
msgid "``WASM_MEM_MAX``: Valid values: MAXIMUM_MEMORY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3551
msgid "``BINARYEN_MEM_MAX``: Valid values: MAXIMUM_MEMORY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3552
msgid ""
"``BINARYEN_PASSES``: Use BINARYEN_EXTRA_PASSES to add additional passes "
"(Valid values: [''])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3553
msgid ""
"``SWAPPABLE_ASM_MODULE``: Fully swappable asm modules are no longer "
"supported (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3554
msgid "``ASM_JS``: asm.js output is not supported anymore (Valid values: [1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3555
msgid ""
"``FINALIZE_ASM_JS``: asm.js output is not supported anymore (Valid values: "
"[0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3556
msgid "``ASYNCIFY_WHITELIST``: Valid values: ASYNCIFY_ONLY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3557
msgid "``ASYNCIFY_BLACKLIST``: Valid values: ASYNCIFY_REMOVE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3558
msgid ""
"``EXCEPTION_CATCHING_WHITELIST``: Valid values: EXCEPTION_CATCHING_ALLOWED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3559
msgid ""
"``SEPARATE_ASM``: Separate asm.js only made sense for fastcomp with asm.js "
"output (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3560
msgid ""
"``SEPARATE_ASM_MODULE_NAME``: Separate asm.js only made sense for fastcomp "
"with asm.js output (Valid values: [''])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3561
msgid ""
"``FAST_UNROLLED_MEMCPY_AND_MEMSET``: The wasm backend implements memcpy/"
"memset in C (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3562
msgid ""
"``DOUBLE_MODE``: The wasm backend always implements doubles normally (Valid "
"values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3563
msgid ""
"``PRECISE_F32``: The wasm backend always implements floats normally (Valid "
"values: [0, 1, 2])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3564
msgid ""
"``ALIASING_FUNCTION_POINTERS``: The wasm backend always uses a single index "
"space for function pointers, in a single Table (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3565
msgid ""
"``AGGRESSIVE_VARIABLE_ELIMINATION``: Wasm ignores asm.js-specific "
"optimization flags (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3566
msgid ""
"``SIMPLIFY_IFS``: Wasm ignores asm.js-specific optimization flags (Valid "
"values: [1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3567
msgid ""
"``DEAD_FUNCTIONS``: The wasm backend does not support dead function removal "
"(Valid values: [[]])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3568
msgid ""
"``WASM_BACKEND``: Only the wasm backend is now supported (note that setting "
"it as -s has never been allowed anyhow) (Valid values: [-1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3569
msgid "``EXPORT_BINDINGS``: No longer needed (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3570
msgid ""
"``RUNNING_JS_OPTS``: Fastcomp cared about running JS which could alter asm."
"js validation, but not upstream (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3571
msgid "``EXPORT_FUNCTION_TABLES``: No longer needed (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3572
msgid "``BINARYEN_SCRIPTS``: No longer needed (Valid values: [''])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3573
msgid "``WARN_UNALIGNED``: No longer needed (Valid values: [0, 1])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3574
msgid "``ASM_PRIMITIVE_VARS``: No longer needed (Valid values: [[]])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3575
msgid ""
"``WORKAROUND_IOS_9_RIGHT_SHIFT_BUG``: Wasm2JS does not support iPhone 4s, "
"iPad 2, iPad 3, iPad Mini 1, Pod Touch 5 (devices with end-of-life at iOS "
"9.3.5) and older (Valid values: [0])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/settings_reference.rst:3576
msgid "``RUNTIME_FUNCS_TO_IMPORT``: No longer needed (Valid values: [[]])"
